                     <interp inst="t18211205-93-person1091" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . My brother left a box-glass with me, the latter end of July. I am a schoolmaster, and live in the <placeName id="t18211205-93-crimeloc578">Hackney-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18211205-93-crimeloc578" type="placeName" value="Hackney-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18211205-93-crimeloc578" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18211205-93-off575 t18211205-93-crimeloc578"></join>; the prisoner, occasionally, came to <rs id="t18211205-93-deflabel579" type="occupation">assist in the house</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18211205-93-defend1087 t18211205-93-deflabel579"></join>; the box was in the parlour, it was locked, and my brother had the key; they were missed about the middle of November; I had discharged the prisoner about a week before; I did not know the contents of the box.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18211205-93-person1092">
                  ELIZA 
                  HESSE
               <interp inst="t18211205-93-person1092" type="surname" value="HESSE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18211205-93-person1092" type="given" value="ELIZA"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18211205-93-person1092" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the wife of the prosecutor, I went to the prisoner on a Monday, and asked if she had the things; she said she had pawned them. I had told her she had better confess; she took me to the pawnbroker, where I redeemed my gold ring. I found the other ring in pawn. I have not found the cross.</p>
               <p>
            
